An instructional faculty member is eligible for PPL if they meet one of the following conditions:

- Have had at least four (4) consecutive fall/spring semesters (e.g. two (2) academic years) of prior employment as a faculty member with the University; 
- Be currently employed under a contract that has a term of at least four (4) years; 
- Be employed fulltime in one of Rice University’s teaching professor ranks at the assistant, associate, or full level.
